<dl id="n40101b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40101b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40101b"> 101(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ be to A for / ever &amp; ever ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So he perished and fared to Jahannam-fire and the dwelling-place dire. Even so it is said of books:&mdash;Whoever diggeth for his brother a pit shall himself fall into it and whoever setteth up a snare for his neighbour shall be snared therein.&rdquo; And this much know we anent the Say of Hakyar the Sage, and magnification be to Allah for ever and ever, AMEN. TMT. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.30</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c10004f" href="c10all.htm#c10004f">VI.C.10:004(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
